FBIS4-29131 "dreas116_j_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 Indonesia Deputy Minister Meets Seoul Envoys in Tehran Deputy Minister Meets Seoul Envoys in Tehran LD1506190394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506190394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] 'Ala'eddin Borujerdi, deputy foreign minister for Asian-Pacific affairs, met ambassadors from North Korea and South Korea in separate meetings today. Borujerdi noted the Islamic Republic of Iran's profound concern over increasing tension in the Korean peninsula. Borujerdi emphasized that Tehran believes direct talks between the two Koreas are the best way to solve current problems. The North Korean envoy said that American actions are the main cause of problems between the two Koreas. The envoy stressed that North Korean officials are ready to solve problems of the two Koreas through negotiations. The South Korean envoy stated Seoul's readiness to solve existing problems between the two Koreas via direct negotiations. The South Korean envoy said that the Islamic Republic of Iran, through its good relations with the two Koreas, can play an effective role in reducing tension between the two Koreas.
